This paper deals with privacy concerns in cloud-based malware checking, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a solution using trusted hardware, which involves hardware architecture and implementation details, making it relevant to distributed computing (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses data structures and performance analysis, which are relevant to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and programming languages (cs.PL).
